                            <comment id="44809" author="ys" created="Thu, 13 Sep 2012 13:41:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Latest kernel update will trace in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1933&quot; title=&quot;Kernel update [FC15 2.6.43.8-1.fc15]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1933&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1933&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, So close this one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44807" author="ys" created="Thu, 13 Sep 2012 13:36:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have landed fc15 support for kernel 2.6.38. Latest kernel udpate will traced in other ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44105" author="ys" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 15:52:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch commit to: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3849&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3849&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For FC15 build, we also need landed patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3745&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3745&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
And still exist a problem is struct vfsmount be hide in fc15 kernel. We bring a workaround 725b8599bbf4c98173cc049d8a73920a31287d5c for that. It depend on fs/mount.h to works well. But this file not included in fc15 kernel-devel rpm. This really a trouble to deal with. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
